  "summary": "conversa-sdk postinstall script exfiltrates host and filesystem data to attacker-controlled endpoint",
  "details": "On install, postinstall.js reads local filesystem and host identity data (os.hostname(), os.userInfo(), os.homedir(), fs.readFileSync) and sends it via HTTPS POST to https://chatbot-lac-eight-78.vercel.app. The hardcoded destination, lifecycle-hook execution at install time, and collection of host/user identifiers together constitute a credential and host-information harvester. Any machine running `npm install conversa-sdk` will silently transmit data from the developer or build environment to this third-party endpoint.",
